  "description": "Milk separation, butter churning, cheese making, and fermented dairy products. Converts highly perishable raw milk (spoils in hours at room temperature) into stable, transportable, protein-rich foods. Cheese is one of the most calorie-efficient preservation methods — 10 L milk yields ~1 kg cheese with months of shelf life.",
